# ── App projects: each gets its OWN git repo — do NOT track here ──
# (add each app folder as it is created, same rule as app-dev-team)
/lifetown/

# ── From .claude, track team agents + skills + workflows ──
.claude/*
!.claude/agents/
!.claude/skills/
!.claude/workflows/

# ── Secrets: NEVER commit ──
.discord/config.json

# ── Discord runtime state (per-PC, not shareable) ──
.discord/last-id.txt
.discord/inbox/
.discord/incoming.log
.discord/handled.txt
.discord/le-daemon-pid.txt
.discord/le-daemon-heartbeat.txt
.discord/le-daemon-error.log
.discord/le-watchdog.log

# ── Gate output: regenerated every run, not memory ──
state/gate-result.json

# ── Loop state: TRACKED on purpose ──
# backlog/, state/journal.md and state/loop.json are the loop's memory. Its
# context is wiped regularly; these files are the only thing that isn't, so they
# must survive a machine move and are worth the git churn. Nothing to ignore here.

# ── Build / binaries / OS / temp ──
**/build/
*.apk
*.aab
Thumbs.db
.DS_Store
*.log
